===Noun===
'''[[посёлок]] [[городской|городского]] [[тип|типа]]''' (posjólok gorodskóvo típa) ''m'', посёлки городского типа (posjólki gorodskóvo típa) ''pl''

#[[townlet]], [[urban]]-[[type]] [[settlement]]
#workers’ town; factory housing estate
:Note: denotes a Russian administrative unit that is similar to a village, but with a special purpose and an urban [[infrastructure]]. The population is no more than 3000 inhabitants, and the settlement is usually centered around a single industry. Most '''townlets''' are built around factories, mines or power stations, but some are like health resorts and have a [[sanitarium]] and health facilities. There are also [[dacha]] '''townlets''', constructed around private recreation as a summer or weekend retreat.

